# Quidax design system (Claude Design)

Read **CLAUDE.md** in the repo root for full Claude-design MCP workflow and project layout.

## Critical rules

- Brand purple is **#6100A5** → `var(--color-brand)` in `src/styles/tokens.css`. Never hardcode hex in components.
- Text: `var(--foreground)` (#201749), muted: `var(--foreground-contrast)` (#4C4A55).
- Surfaces: `#F7F7F7`, `#F2F2EC`, borders `#DEDEDE` / `#E3E2E2` — use token names in tokens.css.
- Typeface: **Uncut Sans Variable** (`src/styles/fonts.css`, `var(--font-family-sans)`). Font file is `public/fonts/Uncut Sans Variable.ttf` (TTF/variable). Use semantic type tokens (`var(--text-body-sm-size)`, `var(--text-caption-size)`, etc.) — no ad-hoc rem/px font sizes.
- Spacing: 4px base scale (`--space-*`, `--gap-*`). Section padding: `--section-padding-y`. Use `gap` with `--gap-md` default.
- Figma flow: `get_design_context` → `get_screenshot` → implement with CSS Modules + tokens (not raw Tailwind from MCP).
- UI primitives go in `src/components/ui/`. Use MCP asset URLs directly; do not add icon libraries for Figma-provided assets.

## Existing components (`src/components/ui/`)

| Component | File | Notes |
|-----------|------|-------|
| Alert | `Alert/Alert.tsx` | info / success / warning / error variants |
| Avatar | `Avatar/Avatar.tsx` | initials fallback |
| Chip | `Chip/Chip.tsx` | label chip / tag |
| CoinRow | `CoinRow/CoinRow.tsx` | crypto asset list row |
| Divider | `Divider/Divider.tsx` | horizontal rule |
| NavBar | `NavBar/NavBar.tsx` | top navigation bar |
| StatCard | `StatCard/StatCard.tsx` | metric / stat display card |
| Tab / TabBar | `Tab/Tab.tsx`, `Tab/TabBar.tsx` | tab + tab bar container |
| Toggle | `Toggle/Toggle.tsx` | boolean toggle switch |
| TransactionRow | `TransactionRow/TransactionRow.tsx` | transaction list row |

All exported from `src/components/ui/index.ts`. Check here before creating new primitives.

## Known token violations to fix

- All component CSS files use hardcoded `rem` values for `font-size` instead of semantic tokens (e.g. `0.875rem` → `var(--text-body-sm-size)`). When editing or adding to a component, migrate its font sizes to token references.
